summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling resolution 1958 (2010), 
Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United Nations,

1. Reaffirms its call for the Government of Iraq to provide without delay payments; 
2. Authorizes the Secretary-General to maintain escrow accounts, retaining funds until 30 June 2017, then transferring remaining funds to the Government of Iraq; 
3. Requests the Secretary-General to implement paragraph 7 and other relevant aspects of resolution 1958 (2010); 
4. Requests the Secretary-General to report on implementation by 30 March 2017 and with a final report three months after transferring remaining funds; 
5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
